<span style="display: block; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Courier;">**__Contention 2__- by implying that states are bound to morality, we prevent the protection natural rights** </span></span>
<span style="display: block; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Courier;">Political realism tells us that states must protect the natural rights of their citizens above any other obligation. In order to protect the natural rights of citizens, the state must have the means to enforce it that are immoral but justified. In order to protect citizens from harm by means of invasion, states need a standing army. A standing army must use lethal methods to secure the security of citizens. A state also requires a police force, but without the ability to, on occasion, use lethal force; the law cannot be enforced and is utterly meaningless. **Thus, a state must use justified yet immoral means in order to protect its citizens.** </span></span>
<span style="display: block; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Courier;">**__Contention 3__- in order to protect the natural rights of citizens, we must look towards political realism** </span></span>
<span style="display: block; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Courier;">In order to best protect the natural rights of citizens, a state must be separated from morality and instead resort to political realism. Thus, states have no moral imperatives in the first place, as they must resort to political realism. Since states have no moral imperatives whatsoever, they have no moral imperative to not possess nuclear weapons. **Thus, by states not having a moral imperative not to possess nuclear weapons, you can effectively negate the resolution as I have proven that there is no reason for a state to not possess nuclear weapons**</span></span><span style="display: block; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;"> </span><span style="display: block; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Courier;">**Neg Case 2- Nuclear Umbrella**</span></span><span style="display: block; line-height: 150%; text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: Courier;">**resolved: states ought not posses nuclear weapons. I negate the resolution**

